  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fluffy Pancakes. An American family-table recipe — generous, comforting, built for a crowd. Adjustable for what you need."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cake batters reward weighing over scooping. Room-temperature butter and eggs, raised properly, tested with a skewer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What you need"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "defaultServings": 4,
          "items": [
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "plain-flour",
              "amount": 1.5,
              "unit": "cup",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "baking-powder",
              "amount": 4,
              "unit": "tsp",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine",
              "amount": 1,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "caster-sugar",
              "amount": 3,
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": true,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "eggs",
              "amount": 1,
              "unit": "each",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "whole-milk",
              "amount": 1.25,
              "unit": "cup",
              "prepNote": "or almond milk",
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "salted-butter",
              "amount": 1,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "or vegan butter",
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "vanilla-extract",
              "amount": 1,
              "unit": "tsp",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "In a large bowl add the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use a whisk or wooden spoon to combine the ingredients together well. Set to the side."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "In a smaller bowl crack in the egg. Pour in the milk and vanilla extract."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Melt the butter in the microwave or in a small saucepan over low heat and add to the bowl."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use a fork or whisk to mix the ingredients together until well combined."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Make a well in the dry ingredients and pour in the wet."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fold the batter together with a wooden spoon until there is no longer any dry flour. There will be a few small lumps in the batter, this is perfectly okay. Make sure to not over mix the batter as this will cause your pancakes to be rubbery and tough."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat a heavy based frypan like a cast iron skillet over medium low heat. When the pan is hot add a knob of butter and wait until it melts."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Measure out ⅓ cup of the pancake batter and pour it into the pan. Let it spread on its own."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cook the pancake for 2-3 minutes or until the edges are set and bubbles are popping in the middle."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use a spatula to flip the pancake over and cook for a further 2-3 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Repeat with the remaining batter."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Serving the Pancakes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Serve the pancakes stacked high, topped with butter and maple syrup!"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Cake sinks in the middle",
              "cause": "Underbaked, or the oven door opened too early.",
              "fix": "Test with a skewer — it should come out with a few moist crumbs, not wet batter. Don't open the oven before three-quarters of the bake time."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Cake is dry",
              "cause": "Overbaked, or too much flour measured by cup not weight.",
              "fix": "Check at the minimum bake time and every five minutes after. Weigh flour for cake recipes — cup measures vary by 20% depending on how you scoop."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Top cracked or domed",
              "cause": "Oven too hot, or batter too thick.",
              "fix": "Drop the temperature by 10°C and check earlier. Domed cakes can be trimmed flat once cool."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Cake didn't rise",
              "cause": "Raising agent stale or omitted, or butter and eggs cold.",
              "fix": "Check baking powder is fresh — it loses lift after six months. Use room-temperature butter and eggs so the batter holds air."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Citrus version: replace the vanilla with the zest of an orange or lemon."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Nut-free: swap ground almonds for desiccated coconut or extra plain flour, weight for weight."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A classic American home recipe — generous, comforting, made for a crowd. The proportions are heartier than the British equivalent; the method is built for a Sunday afternoon."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
